  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-saving Food Security Assistance  to IDPs from East Ghoutta through hot meals provisioning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The present proposal aims to set up a collective kitchen in the new shelter, Karnak Transportation site, that will host around 8000 individuals. During the first week of the implementation COOPI will set up a community kitchen in coordination with TGH and SARC in charge of the sanitation and minimum hygiene requirements already agreed. COOPI has already coordinated with ICRC and SARC the purchases procedures in order to speed up the process at the same time that follows COOPI&apos;s and OCHA&apos;s protocols. 
COOPI will receive from SARC the list of PoCs and their specificities (number of children, pregnant women, persons with special needs...) in order to adapt the distribution of food to their specific requirements.
COOPI will hire IDPs from the shelter to help in the cooking process with COOPI volunteers in order to provide alternative resources to the persons of concern and encourage the community participation in the implementation process. These IDPs will be also in charge of providing inputs from the community to COOPI staff to monitor complaints and ideas for the best distribution. 
The kitchen will distribute one hot meal per person (a menu amounting 2100kcal) during 4 months.</narrative>
  </description>
